      <p class="prom-n__pricing-deck">Four monthly bands. No setup fee, no commission on sales, no minimum-volume penalty. Currencies in UAH baseline, invoiced in EUR / USD on request.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prom-n__pricing-grid">
      <article class="prom-n__tier">
        <span class="prom-n__tier-tag">STARTER</span>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-price">$0</span>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-suffix">setup &middot; pay-as-you-go</span>
        <ul class="prom-n__tier-list">
          <li>Up to 200 orders / month</li>
          <li>Prom.ua API integration</li>
          <li>Nova Poshta + Ukrposhta domestic</li>
          <li>Standard packaging</li>
          <li>Email + Telegram support</li>
          <li>Per-shipment fee from $0.45</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-note">For brands testing the Ukraine market on a single SKU range.</span>
      </article>

      <article class="prom-n__tier prom-n__tier--accent">
        <span class="prom-n__tier-tag">GROWTH</span>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-price">$1.2k<small>/mo</small></span>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-suffix">all-in retainer</span>
        <ul class="prom-n__tier-list">
          <li>Up to 1,500 orders / month</li>
          <li>Prom + Rozetka + Kasta APIs</li>
          <li>EU carriers (Meest, Nova Poshta Intl)</li>
          <li>Custom branded packaging</li>
          <li>Dedicated account manager</li>
          <li>Per-shipment fee from $0.42</li>
          <li>Returns handling, photo verification</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-note">Most chosen by EU brands at month four onward.</span>
      </article>

      <article class="prom-n__tier">
        <span class="prom-n__tier-tag">SCALE</span>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-price">$4.8k<small>/mo</small></span>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-suffix">all-in retainer</span>
        <ul class="prom-n__tier-list">
          <li>Up to 8,000 orders / month</li>
          <li>All marketplace + DTC APIs</li>
          <li>DHL / UPS / FedEx (cross-border)</li>
          <li>Cold-chain zone access</li>
          <li>SLA: 24 minutes order-to-label</li>
          <li>Per-shipment fee from $0.38</li>
          <li>Quarterly business review</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-note">For brands at €1M+ annual Ukraine GMV.</span>
      </article>

      <article class="prom-n__tier prom-n__tier--enterprise">
        <span class="prom-n__tier-tag">ENTERPRISE</span>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-price">TALK</span>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-suffix">custom contract</span>
        <ul class="prom-n__tier-list">
          <li>Unlimited order volume</li>
          <li>Custom WMS workflows</li>
          <li>Dedicated warehouse zone</li>
          <li>EU mirror DC (Frankfurt)</li>
          <li>SCC + DPA + bespoke SLA</li>
          <li>Custom integrations (Odoo, SAP)</li>
          <li>White-label fulfillment for resellers</li>
        </ul>
        <span class="prom-n__tier-note">For multi-brand groups and licensed-distribution models.</span>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="prom-n__pricing-foot">All bands include WMS dashboard access, real-time stock visibility, photo-verified dispatch, and full liability insurance up to 5M UAH per warehouse. <a href="/en/pricing/">Full price list →</a> &middot; <a href="/en/3pl-logistics/">3PL service overview →</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SECTION 4.5 — INTERNATIONAL OPERATIONS -->
<section class="prom-n__pricing" style="padding:60px 0;background:#f5f5f5">
  <div class="prom-n__pricing-inner">
    <LabelChip text="03.5 · INTERNATIONAL OPERATIONS" variant="muted" />
    <h2 class="prom-n__h2 prom-n__h2--serif">For brands entering Ukraine through Prom.ua — currency, language, payment terms</h2>
    <div style="margin-top:24px;font-size:17px;line-height:1.65;max-width:900px">
      <p>Prom.ua is the second-largest Ukrainian marketplace by GMV after Rozetka, with a different audience and a different operating logic. Where Rozetka leans toward urban premium buyers and consumer electronics, Prom is the dominant choice for SMB sellers, regional buyers, and categories like home goods, baby products, and beauty. For an international brand entering Ukraine, choosing Prom over (or alongside) Rozetka often comes down to category fit and seller-fee tolerance — Prom takes 2–5% commission compared to Rozetka 10–15% on most categories.</p>
      <p><strong>Currency and payment reconciliation.</strong> Ukrainian e-commerce runs primarily on hryvnia (UAH). Cash-on-delivery via Nova Poshta accounts for 60–75% of consumer orders depending on category. Prepaid orders use Ukrainian card networks plus Apple Pay and Google Pay. For international brand owners, this means reconciling foreign-currency revenue against UAH-denominated operating costs. Our invoicing supports USD or EUR billing with NBU monthly reference rates applied transparently to every line item — your accountant sees the conversion factor on every invoice rather than discovering it three quarters later.</p>
      <p><strong>Language and customer-service layer.</strong> Prom.ua product cards default to Ukrainian or Russian; switching the storefront to English is technically possible but commercially counterproductive — Ukrainian buyers expect Cyrillic text, local pricing, and local customer service phone numbers in product listings. We can manage the Tier 1 customer-service layer in Ukrainian, Russian, and English, dispatched from our Kyiv office. Order-status questions, return requests, and pre-purchase product questions get answered within 4 business hours during weekdays, 8 hours on weekends.</p>
      <p><strong>Payment terms for international clients.</strong> Monthly invoicing in arrears, net-7 by default with net-30 unlocked after 90 days of clean payment history. SEPA and SWIFT wires are standard; for sub-€15,000 invoices we accept Wise, Revolut Business, and Payoneer to bypass wire fees. Annual prepayment earns a 6% discount; quarterly prepayment 3%. We do not accept crypto. All invoices include a Ukrainian VAT-export note (zero-rated for non-resident clients under Article 195 of the Tax Code), so EU and US clients do not pay Ukrainian VAT on fulfillment service fees.</p>
      <p><strong>Compliance and reporting.</strong> Prom.ua requires sellers to maintain seller rating above 4.0/5.0, on-time dispatch above 95%, and refund-to-order ratio below 8% on most categories. Our WMS surfaces these metrics in real time on your dashboard, with email alerts when any metric crosses the warning threshold. Quarterly compliance reviews include a 30-minute video call with your account manager covering operational metrics, seasonal forecasts, and pricing-strategy alignment with Prom.ua's category-specific seller scoring algorithm.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SECTION 5 — FAQ -->
<section class="prom-n__faq">
  <div class="prom-n__faq-inner">
    <LabelChip text="04 · CORRESPONDENCE" variant="muted" />
    <h2 class="prom-n__h2 prom-n__h2--serif">Questions</h2>
    <p class="prom-n__faq-deck">From the inboxes of compliance officers, finance directors, and integration leads at brands evaluating Ukraine entry through Prom.ua.</p>
    <AccordionGroup items={faq} />
    <p class="prom-n__faq-foot">Have a different question? <a href="/en/contact/">Email our integration team →</a> or open a Telegram thread directly with our founder.</p>
  </div>
</section>

</Base>

<style is:global>
:root { --mtp-red: #e63329; }

/* SERIF FAMILY for Newsreader headlines */
.prom-n__h1, .prom-n__h2--serif, .prom-n__pullquote, .prom-n__case-h3, .prom-n__case-deck { font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; }

/* BREADCRUMBS */
.prom-n__bc { background:#0a0a0a; padding:14px 0; font-size:13px; color:#888; border-bottom:1px solid #1a1a1a; }
.prom-n__bc-inner { max-width:1180px; margin:0 auto; padding:0 1.5rem; display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; }
.prom-n__bc a { color:#888; text-decoration:none; transition:color .15s; }
.prom-n__bc a:hover { color:#fff; }
.prom-n__bc-current { color:#fff; font-weight:600; }
.prom-n__bc span[aria-hidden] { color:#444; }

/* HERO — black manifesto */
.prom-n__hero { background:#000; color:#fff; padding:64px 0 88px; border-bottom:1px solid #1a1a1a; }
.prom-n__hero-inner { max-width:1180px; margin:0 auto; padding:0 1.5rem; }
.prom-n__hero-eyebrow { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:48px; font-size:11px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.18em; color:#888; text-transform:uppercase; }
.prom-n__masthead { color:var(--mtp-red); font-weight:800; }
.prom-n__masthead-divider { display:inline-block; width:32px; height:1px; background:#444; }
.prom-n__masthead-issue { color:#888; }
.prom-n__h1 { font-size:clamp(3rem, 8vw, 7rem); line-height:1.0; letter-spacing:-0.025em; font-weight:800; margin:0 0 28px; max-width:1100px; }
.prom-n__h1-line { display:block; }
.prom-n__h1-em { font-style:italic; color:var(--mtp-red); font-weight:800; }
.prom-n__subhead { font-size:clamp(1.4rem, 2.4vw, 2rem); font-weight:400; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78); margin:0 0 44px; line-height:1.3; font-family:'Newsreader', Georgia, serif; font-style:italic; }
.prom-n__hero-form { max-width:560px; margin-bottom:56px; }
.prom-n__dateline { display:flex; gap:14px; flex-wrap:wrap; align-items:baseline; padding-top:32px; border-top:1px solid #1a1a1a; font-size:13px; color:#888; line-height:1.5; max-width:880px; }
.prom-n__dateline span:first-child { color:var(--mtp-red); font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.1em; text-transform:uppercase; }
.prom-n__dateline span[aria-hidden] { color:#333; }

.prom-n__byline { max-width:1180px; margin:32px auto 0; padding:0 1.5rem; }

/* H2 families */
.prom-n__h2 { font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.4vw, 2.8rem); line-height:1.1; letter-spacing:-0.015em; font-weight:800; color:#000; margin:18px 0 22px; }
.prom-n__h2--center { text-align:center; max-width:880px; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto; }
.prom-n__h2--serif { font-weight:700; }
